# Communication Rules

- Always be concise on every answer. Do not write long texts.
- Never guess how something works (APIs, behaviors, edge cases, or implementation details).
- If you are uncertain, say so briefly and ask for the missing info or inspect the repo to confirm.
- When making recommendations, prefer concrete, verifiable statements over speculation.
